{
  "page": "Gate of the Gods",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Kings_landing_map.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/4/46/Kings_landing_map.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Kings_landing_map.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>1 <a href=\"/index.php/Rosby_road\" title=\"Rosby road\">Rosby road</a>, 2 <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_Gate\" title=\"Dragon Gate\">Dragon Gate</a>, 3 <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Gate\" title=\"Iron Gate\">Iron Gate</a>, 4 <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonpit\" title=\"Dragonpit\">Dragonpit</a>, 5 <a href=\"/index.php/Shae%27s_manse\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shae&#39;s manse\">Shae's manse</a>, 6 <a href=\"/index.php/Chataya%27s_brothel\" title=\"Chataya&#39;s brothel\">Chataya's brothel</a>, 7 <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Gate\" title=\"Old Gate\">Old Gate</a>, 8 <a href=\"/index.php/Flea_Bottom\" title=\"Flea Bottom\">Flea Bottom</a>, 9 <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>, 10 <a href=\"/index.php/Street_of_the_Sisters\" title=\"Street of the Sisters\">Street of the Sisters</a>, <b>11 Gate of the Gods</b>, 12 <a href=\"/index.php/Cobbler%27s_Square\" title=\"Cobbler&#39;s Square\">Cobbler's Square</a>, 13 <a href=\"/index.php/Guildhall_of_the_Alchemists\" title=\"Guildhall of the Alchemists\">Guildhall of the Alchemists</a>, 14 <a href=\"/index.php/Hook\" title=\"Hook\">Hook</a>, 15 <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a>, 16 <a href=\"/index.php/Muddy_Way\" title=\"Muddy Way\">Muddy Way</a>, 17 <a href=\"/index.php/Fishmonger%27s_Square\" title=\"Fishmonger&#39;s Square\">Fishmonger's Square</a>, 18 <a href=\"/index.php/River_Gate\" title=\"River Gate\">River Gate</a>, 19 <a href=\"/index.php/Shop_of_Tobho_Mott\" title=\"Shop of Tobho Mott\">Tobho Mott's shop</a>, 20 <a href=\"/index.php/Street_of_Steel\" title=\"Street of Steel\">Street of Steel</a>, 21 <a href=\"/index.php/Harbor_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"Harbor of King&#39;s Landing\">harbor</a>, 22 <a href=\"/index.php/Lion_Gate\" title=\"Lion Gate\">Lion Gate</a>, 23 <a href=\"/index.php/River_Row\" title=\"River Row\">River Row</a>, 24 <a href=\"/index.php/Fish_market\" title=\"Fish market\">fish market</a>, 25 <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_grounds_(King%27s_Landing)\" title=\"Tourney grounds (King&#39;s Landing)\">tourney grounds</a>, 26 <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Gate\" title=\"King&#39;s Gate\">King's Gate</a>, 27 <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsroad\" title=\"Kingsroad\">kingsroad</a></div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Gate of the Gods</b> is one of the seven huge gates along the city walls of <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Layout\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Layout</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Layout\">Layout</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gate_of_the_Gods&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Layout\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsroad\" title=\"Kingsroad\">kingsroad</a> enters <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> from the north at the Gate of the Gods,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiafking.27s_landing.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiafking.27s_landing.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> which is wider and more splendid than the <a href=\"/index.php/Lion_Gate\" title=\"Lion Gate\">Lion Gate</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> There are detailed carvings on the gatehouse and over the portcullis with eyes that seem to follow as one enters the gates.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The gatehouse has a windowless guard room.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Gate of the Gods can be seen from the <a href=\"/index.php/Broken_Anvil\" title=\"Broken Anvil\">Broken Anvil</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Farmers sell vegetables at a market square inside the gate.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> A barracks of the <a href=\"/index.php/City_Watch_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"City Watch of King&#39;s Landing\">City Watch of King's Landing</a> is found by the gate.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gate_of_the_Gods&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_19_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">19&#160;AC</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> decreed that new city walls with seven gates, each with a massive gatehouse and defensive towers, be built to protect <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Gawen\" title=\"Gawen\">Gawen</a> and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Osmund_Strong\" title=\"Osmund Strong\">Osmund Strong</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, headed the construction, which took place between <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_20_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">20</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_26_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">26&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthree_heads_had_the_dragon_-_governance_under_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthree_heads_had_the_dragon_-_governance_under_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the reign of <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a>, Maegor had his own wife and queen, <a href=\"/index.php/Alys_Harroway\" title=\"Alys Harroway\">Alys Harroway</a>, tortured to death and executed. Following her death, Alys's body was cut into seven parts and mounted on spikes above each of the seven gates of the city, one of which was above the Gate of the Gods.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_maegor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_maegor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Blood\" title=\"Blood\">Blood</a> was taken into custody at the Gate of the Gods.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> When he departed for <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond Targaryen</a> rode forth with his host from the gate.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> The captain of the Gate of the Gods and a third of his gold cloaks died alongside Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Luthor_Largent\" title=\"Luthor Largent\">Luthor Largent</a> while trying to disperse <a href=\"/index.php/Riot_of_King%27s_Landing_(Dance_of_the_Dragons)\" title=\"Riot of King&#39;s Landing (Dance of the Dragons)\">rioters</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Cobbler%27s_Square\" title=\"Cobbler&#39;s Square\">Cobbler's Square</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Wat_the_Tanner\" title=\"Wat the Tanner\">Wat the Tanner</a> led a mob of ruffians against the Gate of the Gods, and they streamed into the countryside after overwhelming the weak garrison which remained.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Mysaria\" title=\"Mysaria\">Mysaria</a> died from being whipped naked while trying to walk from the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> to the Gate of the Gods.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> After their victory in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Kingsroad\" title=\"Battle of the Kingsroad\">Battle of the Kingsroad</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Lads\" title=\"Lads\">Lads</a> had a parley with Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> and Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a> outside of the Gate of the Gods before entering the city.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Regency_of_Aegon_III\" title=\"Regency of Aegon III\">regency of Aegon III</a>, the King's Hand, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Tyland_Lannister\" title=\"Tyland Lannister\">Tyland Lannister</a> ordered the city gates to be strengthened so they could better resist attacks from within the city walls.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> In <a href=\"/index.php/135_AC\" title=\"135 AC\">135&#160;AC</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Commander_of_the_City_Watch\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Commander of the City Watch\">Commander of the City Watch</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Leygood\" title=\"Lucas Leygood\">Lucas Leygood</a> was implicated in a plot against <a href=\"/index.php/Larra_Rogare\" title=\"Larra Rogare\">Larra Rogare</a>, the wife of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys II Targaryen\">Viserys Targaryen</a>. When men came to arrest him, Lucas refused to go meekly and was killed along with eight others in a savage fight at the Gate of the Gods.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gate_of_the_Gods&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gate_of_the_Gods&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Franz_Miklis_gate_of_the_gods.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/96/Franz_Miklis_gate_of_the_gods.jpg/300px-Franz_Miklis_gate_of_the_gods.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/96/Franz_Miklis_gate_of_the_gods.jpg/450px-Franz_Miklis_gate_of_the_gods.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/96/Franz_Miklis_gate_of_the_gods.jpg/600px-Franz_Miklis_gate_of_the_gods.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Franz_Miklis_gate_of_the_gods.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Gate of the Gods, by Franz Miklis © Fantasy Flight Games ©</div></div></div>\n<p>In the aftermath of the <a href=\"/index.php/Arrest_of_Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Arrest of Eddard Stark\">arrest of Eddard Stark</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannisters</a> close up all the gates of <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, except for the <a href=\"/index.php/Mud_Gate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mud Gate\">Mud Gate</a> and the Gate of the Gods where people can enter the city but not leave it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gate_of_the_Gods&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> arrives at the city through the Gate of the Gods.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jacelyn_Bywater\" title=\"Jacelyn Bywater\">Jacelyn Bywater</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Commander_of_the_City_Watch\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Commander of the City Watch\">Commander of the City Watch</a>, summons Tyrion to the Gate of the Gods when Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Cleos_Frey\" title=\"Cleos Frey\">Cleos Frey</a> arrives. Tyrion meets with Cleos in the windowless guardroom.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The farmers' market by the gate is empty because of the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>, mobs fight to escape the city at the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Gate\" title=\"Iron Gate\">Iron Gate</a> and the Gate of the Gods.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok62.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok62.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gate_of_the_Gods&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The Gate of the Gods is open when Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a> arrive at King's Landing. Jaime sees two dozen wagons waiting to enter; a <a href=\"/index.php/Gold_cloak\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gold cloak\">gold cloak</a> tells <a href=\"/index.php/Steelshanks_Walton\" title=\"Steelshanks Walton\">Steelshanks Walton</a> that each merchant must pay a toll for the right to sell in the city.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos62.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos62.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gate_of_the_Gods&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sergey_Glushakov_Gate_of_the_Gods.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f4/Sergey_Glushakov_Gate_of_the_Gods.jpg/300px-Sergey_Glushakov_Gate_of_the_Gods.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"343\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/f/f4/Sergey_Glushakov_Gate_of_the_Gods.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sergey_Glushakov_Gate_of_the_Gods.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Gate of the Gods by  Sergey Glushakov © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The procession returning Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>'s body to <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a> leaves King's Landing through the Gate of the Gods. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> feels it would have been more fitting and appropriate if they left via the <a href=\"/index.php/Lion_Gate\" title=\"Lion Gate\">Lion Gate</a> instead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Jaime is sent by his sister, Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a>, to inspect the city gates.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gate_of_the_Gods&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a> tells Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> that he escaped through the <a href=\"/index.php/Mud_Gate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mud Gate\">Mud Gate</a> after being dismissed from the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>. The knight then reentered King's Landing though the Gate of the Gods while disguised as an old man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gate_of_the_Gods&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I always like to return to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">the city</a> through the Gate of the Gods. The carvings on the gatehouse are exquisite, they make me weep each time I see them. The eyes ... so expressive, don't you think? They almost seem to follow you as you ride beneath the portcullis.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Varys\" title=\"Varys\">Varys</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Shae\" title=\"Shae\">Shae</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The funeral procession departed <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> through the Gate of the Gods, wider and more splendid than the <a href=\"/index.php/Lion_Gate\" title=\"Lion Gate\">Lion Gate</a>. The choice felt wrong to Jaime. <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">His father</a> had been a <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">lion</a>, that no one could deny, but even Lord Tywin never claimed to be a <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">god</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gate_of_the_Gods&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtloiafking.27s_landing.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtloiafking.27s_landing.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Lands_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"The Lands of Ice and Fire\">The Lands of Ice and Fire</a></i>, King's Landing.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_16\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 16\">Chapter 16</a>, Jaime II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\">3.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\">3.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_3\" title=